Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. title: WATCH: Former Fox News editor on calling Arizona for Biden | Jan. 6 hearings
description: Chris Stirewalt, a former Fox News political editor who was fired by the cable network after the 2020 election, testified on June 13 as the House committee investigating the Jan. 6 attack presented its findings to the public.|Prior to his questioning, the Jan. 6 committee presented video clips from interviews with members of former President Donald Trump's inner circle, including former advisors Ivanka Trump, Jared Kushner, Rudy Giuliani, Jason Miller and former campaign manager Bill Stepien.|Stirewalt affirmed that President Joe Biden won the 2020 presidential election. Rep. Zoe Lofgren, D-Calif., asked Stirewalt to explain the concept of a â€œred mirage,â€ which refers to the phenomenon of Democrats voting more often early or absentee compared to Republicans.|â€œSo basically in every election, Republicans win Election Day and Democrats win the early vote,â€ Stirewalt said. He noted that his team made an effort to ensure viewers understood this dynamic, which would be exacerbated given the large number of people who voted ahead of Election Day during the pandemic.|â€œWe had gone to pains -- and I am proud of the pains that we went to -- to make sure that we were informing viewers [about the red mirage] because the Trump campaign and the president had made it clear that they would try to exploit this anomaly,â€ he said.|Stirewalt discussed and defended Fox Newsâ€™ decision to call Arizona for Biden as election results rolled in. He also said he did not believe that Trumpâ€™s attempt to litigate statesâ€™ elections via recounts was likely to succeed.|â€œYouâ€™re better off to play the Powerball than to have that come in,â€ Stirewalt said.|The hearing was the second of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on how Trump actively spread false information about the 2020 election outcome â€“ what has become known as the â€œbig lieâ€ â€“ in the run up to the Jan. 6 insurrection. In the year since its creation, the committee has conducted more than 1,000 interviews, seeking critical information and documents from people witness to, or involved in, the violence that day.|Stream your PBS favorites with the PBS app: https://to.pbs.org/2Jb8twG|Find more from PBS NewsHour at https://www.pbs.org/newshour|Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2HfsCD6|Follow us:|Facebook: http://www.pbs.org/newshour|Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/newshour|Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/newshour

title: Polisi Ungkap Kronologi Laporan Pemukulan Oleh Iko Uwais: Berawal Debat dan Cekcok
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS TV  Aktor Iko Uwais dilaporkan seorang warga di Bekasi atas dugaan pemukulan dan pengeroyokan.||||Hal tersebut dibenarkan oleh Humas Polda Metro Jaya, di mana terdapat laporan ke Polres Metro Bekasi terkait dugaan pemukulan tersebut.||||"Ada seorang warga yang melaporkan adanya pemukulan yang dialaminya, serta pengeroyokan yang dilakukan oleh saudara Iko Uwais," ujar Kombes Endra Zulpan, Kabid Humas Polda Metro Jaya, Selasa (13/6).||||Baca Juga Ini Kronologi Dugaan Iko Uwais Pukul Korban di Bekasi, Berawal Saat Ditagih Pelunasan Jasa Desain di https://www.kompas.tv/article/298521/ini-kronologi-dugaan-iko-uwais-pukul-korban-di-bekasi-berawal-saat-ditagih-pelunasan-jasa-desain||||Adapun kronologi pelaporan dugaan pemukulan yang dilakukan Iko Uwais berawal dari persoalan pribadi antara pelapor dan Iko.||||"Persoalannya adalah persoalan di antara mereka, ada kepentingan antara mereka, kemudian ada cekcok yang ditimbulkan," ujar Zulpan.||||"Kemudian setelah itu saudara Iko Uwais melakukan pemukulan, begitu laporannya," lanjutnya.||||Iko Uwais ramai diberitakan karena diduga lakukan pemukulan dan pengeroyokan seorang warga.||||Laporan terkait dugaan pemukulan yang dilakukan Iko Uwais telah dilaporkan seorang warga ke Polres Metro Bekasi.||||Video Editor: Agung Ramdani||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/298575/polisi-ungkap-kronologi-laporan-pemukulan-oleh-iko-uwais-berawal-debat-dan-cekcok

title: How to Direct a Tense Standoff like Denis Villeneuve â€” Sicario Border Scene Breakdown
description: Sicario Border Scene Breakdown â€” How Denis Villeneuve directed a scene with white-knuckle tension and the brutality of violence.|Sicario Border Scene Breakdown â–ºâ–º https://bit.ly/dp-sp|StudioBinder Blog â–ºâ–º http://bit.ly/sb-bl|â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€|Chapters:|00:00 - Intro to Denisâ€™ World of Tension|00:38 - How Denis Villeneuve creates Tension in Sicario|01:37 - Border Scene Breakdown|04:51 - Using Editing to Elevate Tension|07:59 - Continuing the Tension Experience|â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€|Sicario Border Scene Breakdown|The Sicario border scene is one of those scenes that stick with you. Whether it's the hold-your-breath tension or the brutal and unceremonious violence, thereâ€™s no denying this is a well-crafted scene. In this Sicario video essay, weâ€™re going to run through the border scene standoff and shootout to see how director Denis Villeneuve directed tension and trauma.|Denis Villeneuveâ€™s Approach to Violence|In an interview about the Sicario border scene, Villeneuve had this to say. â€œI wanted to have the same approach to violence that I have had in my previous films, which is to seize the point of view of the victims. I wanted to show the brutality of violence, its ugliness, without glorifying it or creating too much of a spectacle.â€ In this case, the victim in question is actually Kate Mercer, the idealistic FBI agent who is traumatized by the violent shootout and the moral compromises being made. So how does Villeneuve accomplish both the unglamorous violence and the trauma that Kate experiences?|Sicario Analysis|There are a few tactics happening in this scene â€” the calm and controlled camera work punctuated by brief moments of disorienting, rapid-fire editing and gunfire. As the border bandits make their move, they are quickly surrounded on all sides by Delta Force operators. As they exit the SUV, Villeneuve cuts between six different shots in seven seconds, all from different angles. Something as mundane as characters exiting a vehicle shouldnâ€™t be so jarring but thereâ€™s a reason for this presentation â€” to make us as panicked and disoriented as Kate is in that moment.|Then the bandits in the red Impala pull their guns but are swiftly executed. Again, we get another quick burst of shots (5 cuts in 3 seconds) â€” the brutality of the action is enhanced by the jarring edits â€” and then we cut to Kateâ€™s incredulous reaction. Once again, the operators dispatch the second car of would-be assassins and the pattern repeats with disorienting cuts followed by Kateâ€™s reaction. The scene ends with a final mini-burst of violence, this time as Kate herself fires her weapon.|As Villeneuve described, we have a tense scene but the violence is treated as coldly and brutally as possible. There is no spectacle or glorifying the violence here â€” just a swift and startling experience for both Kate and the audience.|#FilmTheory #VideoEssay #Filmmaking|â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€|â™¬  SONGS USED:|â€œInto Hellâ€ - Makeup and Vanity Set|â€œMelancholiaâ€ - JÃ³hann JÃ³hannsson|â€œThe Borderâ€ - JÃ³hann JÃ³hannsson|â€œReflectionâ€ - JÃ³hann JÃ³hannsson|â€œConvoyâ€ - JÃ³hann JÃ³hannsson|â€œCicloâ€ - Makeup and Vanity Set|Music by Artlist â–º https://utm.io/umJx|Music by Artgrid â–º https://utm.io/umJy|Music by Soundstripe â–º http://bit.ly/2IXwomF|Music by MusicBed â–º http://bit.ly/2Fnz9Zq|â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€|SUBSCRIBE to StudioBinderâ€™s YouTube channel! â–ºâ–º http://bit.ly/2hksYO0|Looking for a production management solution for your film?
